This paper is primarily focused on image reconstruction and denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for denoising, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of noise modeling for learning-based denoising, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of demosaicking algorithms, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the simulation of camera pipelines, which could fall under the image processing (cs.IR) sub-category.
